ResourceController

Base URL: /api/resources

1. Create a Resource
Endpoint: /api/resources
Method: POST
Description: Creates a new resource.

Request Body:
`json`
{
  "id": <Long>,           // (optional) ID of the resource
  "name": <String>,       // Name of the resource
  "type": <String>,       // Type of the resource (e.g., "human", "equipment")
  "details": <String>,    // Additional details about the resource
  "availability": <Double> // Percentage availability (e.g., 100.0 for fully available)
}
Response:
Status Code: 201 Created
Body: Returns the created resource.
`json`
{
  "id": <Long>,
  "name": <String>,
  "type": <String>,
  "details": <String>,
  "availability": <Double>
}

2. Update a Resource
Endpoint: /api/resources/{resourceId}
Method: PUT
Description: Updates an existing resource.

Path Parameter: resourceId (Long): The ID of the resource to update.
Request Body:
`json`
{
  "name": <String>,       // Updated name of the resource
  "type": <String>,       // Updated type of the resource
  "details": <String>,    // Updated additional details about the resource
  "availability": <Double> // Updated percentage availability
}
Response:
Status Code: 200 OK
Body: Returns the updated resource.
`json`
{
  "id": <Long>,
  "name": <String>,
  "type": <String>,
  "details": <String>,
  "availability": <Double>
}

3. Get Resource by ID
Endpoint: /api/resources/{resourceId}
Method: GET
Description: Retrieves a specific resource by its ID.

Path Parameter: resourceId (Long): The ID of the resource to retrieve.
Response:
Status Code: 200 OK
Body:
`json`
{
  "id": <Long>,
  "name": <String>,
  "type": <String>,
  "details": <String>,
  "availability": <Double>
}
Status Code: 404 Not Found
Returns no body if the resource is not found.

4. Get All Resources
Endpoint: /api/resources
Method: GET
Description: Retrieves a list of all resources.

Response:
Status Code: 200 OK
Body:Returns a list of all resources.
`json`
[
  {
    "id": <Long>,
    "name": <String>,
    "type": <String>,
    "details": <String>,
    "availability": <Double>
  },
  ...
]

5. Delete a Resource
Endpoint: /api/resources/{resourceId}
Method: DELETE
Description: Deletes a specific resource by its ID.

Path Parameter: resourceId (Long): The ID of the resource to delete.
Response:
Status Code: 204 No Content